{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":245,"text":"Mobility in developing world cities"},{"time":3378,"text":"is a very peculiar challenge,"},{"time":5536,"text":"because different from health"},{"time":7341,"text":"or education or housing,"},{"time":9651,"text":"it tends to get worse as societies become richer."},{"time":13085,"text":"Clearly, a unsustainable model."},{"time":15869,"text":"Mobility, as most other developing country problems,"},{"time":20196,"text":"more than a matter of money or technology,"},{"time":24101,"text":"is a matter of equality, equity."},{"time":29492,"text":"The great inequality in developing countries"},{"time":32601,"text":"makes it difficult to see, for example,"},{"time":36026,"text":"that in terms of transport,"},{"time":38590,"text":"an advanced city is not one"},{"time":40520,"text":"where even the poor use cars,"},{"time":42542,"text":"but rather one where even the rich"},{"time":44565,"text":"use public transport."},{"time":46789,"text":"Or bicycles: For example, in Amsterdam,"},{"time":50355,"text":"more than 30 percent of the population"},{"time":52385,"text":"uses bicycles,"},{"time":53920,"text":"despite the fact that the Netherlands has"},{"time":55818,"text":"a higher income per capita than the United States."},{"time":59801,"text":"There is a conflict in developing world cities"},{"time":63658,"text":"for money, for government investment."},{"time":66226,"text":"If more money is invested in highways,"},{"time":68727,"text":"of course there is less money for housing,"},{"time":70739,"text":"for schools, for hospitals,"},{"time":73096,"text":"and also there is a conflict for space."},{"time":77072,"text":"There is a conflict for space between"},{"time":79498,"text":"those with cars and those without them."},{"time":82023,"text":"Most of us accept today"},{"time":83866,"text":"that private property and a market economy"},{"time":86650,"text":"is the best way to manage\nmost of society's resources."},{"time":89848,"text":"However, there is a problem with that,"},{"time":92253,"text":"that market economy needs"},{"time":94921,"text":"inequality of income in order to work."},{"time":97639,"text":"Some people must make more money,"},{"time":99181,"text":"some others less."},{"time":100732,"text":"Some companies succeed. Others fail."},{"time":103301,"text":"Then what kind of equality"},{"time":105175,"text":"can we hope for today"},{"time":106780,"text":"with a market economy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":108702,"text":"I would propose two kinds"},{"time":110638,"text":"which both have much to do with cities."},{"time":112992,"text":"The first one is equality of quality of life,"},{"time":116098,"text":"especially for children,"},{"time":117886,"text":"that all children should have,"},{"time":119541,"text":"beyond the obvious health and education,"},{"time":122548,"text":"access to green spaces, to sports facilities,"},{"time":126407,"text":"to swimming pools, to music lessons."},{"time":129433,"text":"And the second kind of equality"},{"time":131924,"text":"is one which we could call \"democratic equality.\""},{"time":136207,"text":"The first article in every constitution states"},{"time":139156,"text":"that all citizens are equal before the law."},{"time":142445,"text":"That is not just poetry."},{"time":144900,"text":"It's a very powerful principle."},{"time":147101,"text":"For example, if that is true,"},{"time":149687,"text":"a bus with 80 passengers"},{"time":151572,"text":"has a right to 80 times more road space"},{"time":154301,"text":"than a car with one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157173,"text":"We have been so used to inequality, sometimes,"},{"time":161566,"text":"that it's before our noses and we do not see it."},{"time":165297,"text":"Less than 100 years ago,"},{"time":167573,"text":"women could not vote,"},{"time":168960,"text":"and it seemed normal,"},{"time":171166,"text":"in the same way that it seems normal today"},{"time":174850,"text":"to see a bus in traffic."},{"time":177782,"text":"In fact, when I became mayor,"},{"time":180733,"text":"applying that democratic principle"},{"time":183701,"text":"that public good prevails over private interest,"},{"time":186113,"text":"that a bus with 100 people"},{"time":189013,"text":"has a right to 100 times\nmore road space than a car,"},{"time":191587,"text":"we implemented a mass transit system"},{"time":194601,"text":"based on buses in exclusive lanes."},{"time":197070,"text":"We called it TransMilenio,\nin order to make buses sexier."},{"time":201512,"text":"And one thing is that it is also a very beautiful\ndemocratic symbol, because as buses zoom by,"},{"time":209309,"text":"expensive cars stuck in traffic,"},{"time":213473,"text":"it clearly is almost a picture of democracy at work."},{"time":219800,"text":"In fact, it's not just a matter of equity."},{"time":223629,"text":"It doesn't take Ph.D.'s."},{"time":225521,"text":"A committee of 12-year-old children"},{"time":227793,"text":"would find out in 20 minutes"},{"time":229799,"text":"that the most efficient way to use scarce road space"},{"time":233503,"text":"is with exclusive lanes for buses."},{"time":236987,"text":"In fact, buses are not sexy,"},{"time":240309,"text":"but they are the only possible means"},{"time":243456,"text":"to bring mass transit to all areas"},{"time":246739,"text":"of fast growing developing cities."},{"time":250414,"text":"They also have great capacity."},{"time":252589,"text":"For example, this system in Guangzhou"},{"time":255333,"text":"is moving more passengers our direction"},{"time":258038,"text":"than all subway lines in China,"},{"time":260862,"text":"except for one line in Beijing,"},{"time":263353,"text":"at a fraction of the cost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265690,"text":"We fought not just for space for buses,"},{"time":269804,"text":"but we fought for space for people,"},{"time":272860,"text":"and that was even more difficult."},{"time":276073,"text":"Cities are human habitats,"},{"time":278858,"text":"and we humans are pedestrians."},{"time":282587,"text":"Just as fish need to swim or birds need to fly"},{"time":285651,"text":"or deer need to run, we need to walk."},{"time":288443,"text":"There is a really enormous conflict,"},{"time":291774,"text":"when we are talking about developing country cities,"},{"time":294775,"text":"between pedestrians and cars."},{"time":297454,"text":"Here, what you see is a picture that shows"},{"time":300385,"text":"insufficient democracy."},{"time":302037,"text":"What this shows is that people who walk"},{"time":305129,"text":"are third-class citizens"},{"time":306804,"text":"while those who go in cars"},{"time":308139,"text":"are first-class citizens."},{"time":309954,"text":"In terms of transport infrastructure,"},{"time":312361,"text":"what really makes a difference"},{"time":313564,"text":"between advanced and backward cities"},{"time":316110,"text":"is not highways or subways"},{"time":318202,"text":"but quality sidewalks."},{"time":320466,"text":"Here they made a flyover, probably very useless,"},{"time":323232,"text":"and they forgot to make a sidewalk."},{"time":327190,"text":"This is prevailing all over the world."},{"time":329514,"text":"Not even schoolchildren\nare more important than cars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333299,"text":"In my city of Bogot√°,"},{"time":335540,"text":"we fought a very difficult battle"},{"time":338894,"text":"in order to take space from cars,"},{"time":341668,"text":"which had been parking on sidewalks for decades,"},{"time":344564,"text":"in order to make space for people that should reflect"},{"time":347679,"text":"dignity of human beings,"},{"time":349347,"text":"and to make space for protected bikeways."},{"time":352196,"text":"First of all, I had black hair before that."},{"time":354941,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":356917,"text":"And I was almost impeached in the process."},{"time":360173,"text":"It is a very difficult battle."},{"time":362317,"text":"However, it was possible, finally,"},{"time":365494,"text":"after very difficult battles, to make a city"},{"time":368732,"text":"that would reflect some respect for human dignity,"},{"time":371416,"text":"that would show that those who walk are equally"},{"time":373211,"text":"important to those who have cars."},{"time":375032,"text":"Indeed, a very important ideological\nand political issue anywhere"},{"time":379681,"text":"is how to distribute that most valuable resource"},{"time":382627,"text":"of a city, which is road space."},{"time":385036,"text":"A city could find oil or diamonds underground"},{"time":387873,"text":"and it would not be so valuable as road space."},{"time":389964,"text":"How to distribute it between pedestrians,"},{"time":393125,"text":"bicycles, public transport and cars?"},{"time":396227,"text":"This is not a technological issue,"},{"time":399018,"text":"and we should remember that in no constitution"},{"time":402542,"text":"parking is a constitutional right"},{"time":404863,"text":"when we make that distribution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407364,"text":"We also built, and this was 15 years ago,"},{"time":410995,"text":"before there were bikeways in New York"},{"time":412933,"text":"or in Paris or in London,"},{"time":414377,"text":"it was a very difficult battle as well,"},{"time":416824,"text":"more than 350 kilometers of protected bicycle ways."},{"time":421644,"text":"I don't think protected bicycle ways"},{"time":423568,"text":"are a cute architectural feature."},{"time":426322,"text":"They are a right, just as sidewalks are,"},{"time":429028,"text":"unless we believe that only those"},{"time":431226,"text":"with access to a motor vehicle"},{"time":433560,"text":"have a right to safe mobility,"},{"time":435627,"text":"without the risk of getting killed."},{"time":437900,"text":"And just as busways are,"},{"time":441567,"text":"protected bikeways also are"},{"time":443658,"text":"a powerful symbol of democracy,"},{"time":445537,"text":"because they show that a citizen on a $30 bicycle"},{"time":449187,"text":"is equally important"},{"time":451609,"text":"to one in a $30,000 car."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455551,"text":"And we are living in a unique moment in history."},{"time":459268,"text":"In the next 50 years, more than half of those cities"},{"time":463720,"text":"which will exist in the year 2060 will be built."},{"time":468282,"text":"In many developing country cities,"},{"time":470580,"text":"more than 80 and 90 percent"},{"time":472640,"text":"of the city which will exist in 2060"},{"time":477342,"text":"will be built over the next four or five decades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479703,"text":"But this is not just a matter\nfor developing country cities."},{"time":482825,"text":"In the United States, for example,"},{"time":484814,"text":"more than 70 million new homes"},{"time":487479,"text":"must be built over the next 40 or 50 years."},{"time":490176,"text":"That's more than all the homes that today exist"},{"time":493249,"text":"in Britain, France and Canada put together."},{"time":497765,"text":"And I believe that our cities today"},{"time":501122,"text":"have severe flaws,"},{"time":503237,"text":"and that different, better ones could be built."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506795,"text":"What is wrong with our cities today?"},{"time":509243,"text":"Well, for example, if we tell any three-year-old child"},{"time":513477,"text":"who is barely learning to speak"},{"time":515182,"text":"in any city in the world today,"},{"time":516693,"text":"\"Watch out, a car,\""},{"time":518375,"text":"the child will jump in fright,"},{"time":520937,"text":"and with a very good reason, because there are"},{"time":522716,"text":"more than 10,000 children who are killed"},{"time":525273,"text":"by cars every year in the world."},{"time":528742,"text":"We have had cities for 8,000 years,"},{"time":531350,"text":"and children could walk out of home and play."},{"time":535686,"text":"In fact, only very recently,"},{"time":537978,"text":"towards 1900, there were no cars."},{"time":539812,"text":"Cars have been here for really\nless than 100 years."},{"time":543813,"text":"They completely changed cities."},{"time":546587,"text":"In 1900, for example,"},{"time":548535,"text":"nobody was killed by cars in the United States."},{"time":552421,"text":"Only 20 years later,"},{"time":554336,"text":"between 1920 and 1930,"},{"time":557731,"text":"almost 200,000 people"},{"time":560089,"text":"were killed by cars in the United States."},{"time":562599,"text":"Only in 1925, almost 7,000 children"},{"time":566630,"text":"were killed by cars in the United States."},{"time":570582,"text":"So we could make different cities,"},{"time":574585,"text":"cities that will give more priority to human beings"},{"time":577346,"text":"than to cars, that will give more public space"},{"time":579805,"text":"to human beings than to cars,"},{"time":581929,"text":"cities which show great respect"},{"time":584684,"text":"for those most vulnerable citizens,"},{"time":586845,"text":"such as children or the elderly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588629,"text":"I will propose to you a couple of ingredients"},{"time":592434,"text":"which I think would make cities much better,"},{"time":595776,"text":"and it would be very simple to implement them"},{"time":598261,"text":"in the new cities which are only being created."},{"time":601185,"text":"Hundreds of kilometers of greenways"},{"time":604238,"text":"criss-crossing cities in all directions."},{"time":607388,"text":"Children will walk out of homes into safe spaces."},{"time":610132,"text":"They could go for dozens of kilometers safely"},{"time":613093,"text":"without any risk in wonderful greenways,"},{"time":616147,"text":"sort of bicycle highways,"},{"time":618563,"text":"and I would invite you to imagine the following:"},{"time":621668,"text":"a city in which every other street would be"},{"time":624906,"text":"a street only for pedestrians and bicycles."},{"time":629992,"text":"In new cities which are going to be built,"},{"time":632223,"text":"this would not be particularly difficult."},{"time":634768,"text":"When I was mayor of Bogot√°,"},{"time":638295,"text":"in only three years, we were able to create"},{"time":640825,"text":"70 kilometers,"},{"time":642963,"text":"in one of the most dense cities in the world,"},{"time":645459,"text":"of these bicycle highways."},{"time":647826,"text":"And this changes the way people live,"},{"time":651216,"text":"move, enjoy the city."},{"time":653888,"text":"In this picture, you see in one\nof the very poor neighborhoods,"},{"time":656509,"text":"we have a luxury pedestrian bicycle street,"},{"time":659579,"text":"and the cars still in the mud."},{"time":661940,"text":"Of course, I would love to pave this street for cars."},{"time":664763,"text":"But what do we do first?"},{"time":666211,"text":"Ninety-nine percent of the people\nin those neighborhoods don't have cars."},{"time":669372,"text":"But you see, when a city is only being created,"},{"time":671845,"text":"it's very easy to incorporate"},{"time":673935,"text":"this kind of infrastructure."},{"time":676111,"text":"Then the city grows around it."},{"time":678809,"text":"And of course this is just a glimpse"},{"time":681852,"text":"of something which could be much better"},{"time":684647,"text":"if we just create it,"},{"time":686365,"text":"and it changes the way of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688702,"text":"And the second ingredient,\nwhich would solve mobility,"},{"time":692768,"text":"that very difficult challenge in developing countries,"},{"time":695346,"text":"in a very low-cost and simple way,"},{"time":698341,"text":"would be to have hundreds of kilometers"},{"time":702353,"text":"of streets only for buses,"},{"time":704875,"text":"buses and bicycles and pedestrians."},{"time":707979,"text":"This would be, again, a very low-cost solution"},{"time":711018,"text":"if implemented from the start,"},{"time":713341,"text":"low cost, pleasant transit"},{"time":715864,"text":"with natural sunlight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719562,"text":"But unfortunately, reality is not as good"},{"time":724210,"text":"as my dreams."},{"time":725962,"text":"Because of private property of land"},{"time":729144,"text":"and high land prices,"},{"time":732165,"text":"all developing country cities\nhave a large problem of slums."},{"time":735202,"text":"In my country of Colombia, almost half the homes"},{"time":738112,"text":"in cities initially were illegal developments."},{"time":743458,"text":"And of course it's very difficult to have"},{"time":746670,"text":"mass transit or to use bicycles in such environments."},{"time":750626,"text":"But even legal developments"},{"time":752672,"text":"have also been located in the wrong places,"},{"time":755644,"text":"very far from the city centers"},{"time":758445,"text":"where it's impossible to provide"},{"time":760482,"text":"low-cost, high-frequency public transport."},{"time":764313,"text":"As a Latin American, and Latin America"},{"time":767193,"text":"was the most recently organized region in the world,"},{"time":770620,"text":"I would recommend, respectfully, passionately,"},{"time":775780,"text":"to those countries which are yet to urbanize --"},{"time":779890,"text":"Latin America went from 40 percent urban in 1950"},{"time":784911,"text":"to 80 percent urban in 2010 --"},{"time":790984,"text":"I would recommend Asian and African countries"},{"time":794144,"text":"which are yet to urbanize,"},{"time":795926,"text":"such as India which is only 33 percent urban now,"},{"time":800093,"text":"that governments should acquire\nall land around cities."},{"time":803068,"text":"In this way, their cities could grow in the right places"},{"time":805589,"text":"with the right spaces, with the parks,"},{"time":807364,"text":"with the greenways, with the busways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810740,"text":"The cities we are going to build"},{"time":812255,"text":"over the next 50 years"},{"time":814095,"text":"will determine quality of life and even happiness"},{"time":816492,"text":"for billions of people towards the future."},{"time":818646,"text":"What a fantastic opportunity for leaders"},{"time":822224,"text":"and many young leaders to come,"},{"time":824466,"text":"especially in the developing countries."},{"time":826533,"text":"They can create a much happier life"},{"time":828380,"text":"for billions towards the future."},{"time":829949,"text":"I am sure, I am optimistic,"},{"time":831912,"text":"that they will make cities better"},{"time":833820,"text":"than our most ambitious dreams."}]},{"cues":[{"time":836989,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}